  "response": "As of my last update, Voyager 1 has not confirmed or disproven the existence of Planet X or the Nemesis star. Voyager 1, launched in 1977, is primarily tasked with exploring the outer planets and interstellar space, rather than searching for hypothetical celestial bodies like Planet X or Nemesis.\n\nThe concept of Planet X refers to a hypothetical ninth planet in our solar system, existing beyond Pluto. Its existence has been suggested to explain certain gravitational effects observed in the outer solar system, but no direct observational evidence has confirmed its presence as of my last update.\n\nSimilarly, the Nemesis hypothesis suggests a distant companion star to the Sun, which could be responsible for periodic mass extinctions on Earth by sending a shower of comets into the inner solar system. However, extensive surveys and searches have not found any evidence to support the existence of a Nemesis star.\n\nIf there have been any developments or discoveries regarding these hypotheses after October 2023, you may want to look them up in the latest scientific literature or news sources for the most current information.",
